^-|cs||fp||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*BLarry Cohen: ^*N|cp||at|With a balanced hand, this is easy. 2@C-2@D-2NT shows 22-24 balanced (assuming a 2NT opener would have 20-21). With 25-27, rebid 3NT. (After these notrump rebids, Stayman and transfers are on.)|
PG| ***** 22 ***** |


AT|

With an unbalanced hand, opener names his long suit. This is FORCING, but NOT GAME FORCING. It is important to study that last sentence.|
PG| ***** 23 ***** |


cs|6|fp|3|ht|j|at|^-{      A 2@C opener is not a game force.
    For one, 2@C-2@D-2NT can end the auction.    }
^-|fp||
