qx||cs|6|fp|1|ht|b|at|^-{      RESPONDER'S REBID      }
^-|cs||fp||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*BLarry Cohen: ^*N|cp||at|If responder's first bid was something other than 2@D, then all bidding is natural. The partnership must reach at least a game.|
PG| ***** 29 ***** |


AT|

If responder's first bid was 2@D, he can pass a 2NT rebid by opener. What if opener bids a suit? 2@C-P-2@D-P-2@H:|
PG| ***** 30 ***** |


AT|

After opener bids a suit, the most popular approach is to use "cheaper minor second negative." The terminology is a little dated since there was never a "first" negative. Anyway, next are the auctions we are discussing:|
PG| ***** 31 ***** |


